      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''On Avenue C, Renewal and Regret'' calls La Plaza Cultural on Avenue C a garden, but even the ''gardeners'' now call it an ''outdoor performance space'' and claim it should be maintained as such.</p>
        <p>The article says that ''developers want the site.'' Lower East Side Coalition Housing has been granted more than $9 million by HUD to build 80 units of housing for poor senior citizens from the neighborhood. While technically a ''developer,'' it develops housing for low/no income families and formerly homeless families.</p>
        <p>CHRISTINE WIDGREN  New York</p>
        <p>The writer is a board member of Lower East Side Coalition Housing.</p>
      </block>
